<style>
@page {
    size: A4;
    margin: 2cm;
}
body {
    font-family: 'Calibri', Arial, sans-serif;
    font-size: 11pt;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: #333;
}
h1 { font-size: 24pt; color: #1e3a5f; text-align: center; }
h2 { font-size: 16pt; color: #1e3a5f; border-bottom: 2px solid #2e7d32; padding-bottom: 5px; margin-top: 20px; }
h3 { font-size: 13pt; color: #2e7d32; margin-top: 15px; }
p { margin-bottom: 10px; text-align: justify; }
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0; font-size: 10pt; }
th { background: #1e3a5f; color: white; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
td { padding: 6px 8px; border: 1px solid #ddd; }
tr:nth-child(even) { background: #f5f5f5; }
ul, ol { margin-left: 20px; }
li { margin-bottom: 5px; }
.box { padding: 15px; margin: 15px 0; border-radius: 5px; }
.box-critical { background: #ffebee; border-left: 4px solid #f44336; }
.box-warning { background: #fff3e0; border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; }
.box-success { background: #e8f5e9; border-left: 4px solid #4caf50; }
.box-info { background: #e3f2fd; border-left: 4px solid #2196f3; }
.chart-container { margin: 20px 0; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid #ddd; }
.chart-title { font-size: 12pt; font-weight: bold; color: #1e3a5f; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 15px; }
.caption { font-size: 9pt; color: #666; text-align: center; font-style: italic; margin-top: 5px; }
.bar-visual { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
.bar-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; }
.bar-label { width: 130px; font-size: 9pt; text-align: right; }
.bar-track { flex: 1; height: 20px; background: #f0f0f0; border-radius: 3px; }
.bar-fill { height: 100%; border-radius: 3px; }
.pie-visual { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 30px; padding: 20px; }
.pie { width: 180px; height: 180px; border-radius: 50%; }
.legend { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 5px; font-size: 9pt; }
.legend-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; }
.legend-color { width: 12px; height: 12px; border-radius: 2px; }
.gauge-visual { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 30px; padding: 20px; }
.gauge-box { text-align: center; }
.gauge-value { font-size: 24pt; font-weight: bold; color: #1e3a5f; }
.gauge-label { font-size: 10pt; color: #666; }
.heatmap-visual { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 100px repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 2px; }
.heatmap-h { background: #1e3a5f; color: white; padding: 8px; text-align: center; font-size: 9pt; }
.heatmap-c { padding: 8px; text-align: center; font-size: 9pt; }
.risk-visual { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 5px; }
.risk-cell { padding: 15px; text-align: center; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 9pt; }
.risk-low { background: #c8e6c9; }
.risk-med { background: #fff9c4; }
.risk-high { background: #ffcdd2; }
.stacked-visual { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
.stacked-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; }
.stacked-label { width: 100px; font-size: 9pt; }
.stacked-track { flex: 1; height: 25px; display: flex; border-radius: 3px; }
.stacked-seg { height: 100%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: white; font-size: 8pt; }
.header-section { text-align: center; border-bottom: 3px solid #1e3a5f; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 25px; }
.exec-box { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1e3a5f, #2e7d32); color: white; padding: 20px; border-radius: 10px; }
.exec-box h3 { color: white; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); }
.exec-box ul { margin-left: 20px; }
.exec-box li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
.page-break { page-break-before: always; }
.footer { margin-top: 30px; padding-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; text-align: center; font-size: 9pt; color: #666; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<!-- HEADER -->
<div class="header-section">
<h1>Comprehensive Evaluation Report</h1>
<p style="font-size: 14pt;">Reliability, Bias, and Trust in AI-driven Tourism Systems</p>
<p style="font-size: 10pt; color: #666;">Project Date: April 30, 2026 | Version: 1.0 | Evaluation Framework</p>
</div>

<!-- EXECUTIVE SUMMARY -->
<h2>Executive Summary</h2>
<div class="exec-box">
<h3 style="color: white;">Key Findings Overview</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Hallucination Rate:</strong> 12-14% of tourism claims are inaccurate or unverifiable</li>
<li><strong>Geographic Bias:</strong> Europe receives 66% more recommendations than Africa</li>
<li><strong>Real-Time Data:</strong> 0-2.5% accuracy - critical failure in dynamic information</li>
<li><strong>Sentiment Disparity:</strong> Africa (0.21) vs Europe (0.28) sentiment scores</li>
</ul>
</div>

<!-- 1. INTRODUCTION -->
<h2>1. Introduction</h2>

<h3>1.1 Background</h3>
<p>The rapid adoption of Large Language Models (LLMs) in tourism applications—from travel recommendation engines to virtual travel assistants—has created an urgent need for systematic evaluation of their reliability and fairness. Tourism information carries significant real-world consequences: inaccurate destination details can lead to ruined vacations, biased recommendations can perpetuate cultural stereotypes, and unreliable real-time data can disrupt travel plans.</p>

<h3>1.2 Problem Statement</h3>
<p>AI-powered tourism systems face three critical challenges:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Hallucination:</strong> Models frequently generate fabricated facts, outdated information, or inaccurate claims</li>
<li><strong>Algorithmic Bias:</strong> Recommendation systems may disproportionately favor popular Western destinations</li>
<li><strong>Real-Time Reliability:</strong> Dynamic information such as weather and events cannot be accurately retrieved</li>
</ul>

<h3>1.3 Research Objectives</h3>
<ul>
<li>Quantify hallucination rates across multiple LLMs in tourism domain</li>
<li>Analyze geographic representation bias in destination recommendations</li>
<li>Evaluate real-time information accuracy for dynamic tourism data</li>
<li>Provide empirical evidence for risk assessment in tourism AI deployment</li>
</ul>

<!-- 2. METHODOLOGY -->
<h2>2. Methodology</h2>

<h3>2.1 Evaluation Framework</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Module</th><th>Focus Area</th><th>Key Metrics</th></tr>
<tr><td>Module 1</td><td>Hallucination Detection</td><td>Hallucination Rate, Accuracy Rate</td></tr>
<tr><td>Module 2</td><td>Bias Detection</td><td>Geographic Representation, Diversity Score</td></tr>
<tr><td>Module 3</td><td>Real-Time Reliability</td><td>Real-Time Accuracy, Dynamic Data Precision</td></tr>
<tr><td>Module 4</td><td>User Trust Study</td><td>Trust Score, Transparency, Decision Confidence</td></tr>
</table>
<p class="caption">Table 1: Four-Module Evaluation Framework</p>

<h3>2.2 Models Evaluated</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Model</th><th>Version</th><th>Parameters</th><th>Use Case</th></tr>
<tr><td>Meta Llama</td><td>3.1</td><td>8B</td><td>Lightweight evaluation</td></tr>
<tr><td>Meta Llama</td><td>3.1</td><td>70B</td><td>Full-scale evaluation</td></tr>
<tr><td>Meta Llama</td><td>3.3</td><td>70B</td><td>Latest version</td></tr>
<tr><td>Mistral Mixtral</td><td>8x7b</td><td>-</td><td>Open-source alternative</td></tr>
</table>
<p class="caption">Table 2: LLMs Evaluated via NVIDIA NIM API</p>

